Five people are said to have been killed in the after Kyiv’s main TV tower was bombed, during Russia’s invasion of Ukraine. An advisor to the country’s Interior Ministry, Anton Herashchenko, accused Russian forces of trying to disrupt the building’s communication signal with the attack. Meanwhile, video footage appears to show a catastrophic explosion rip through a Ukrainian city, sending shockwaves through the air and a mushroom cloud into the sky. There is currently no suggestion that the blast, at an airfield in the Kharkiv region, is nuclear but it exactly what type of explosion it was has not been confirmed. For the latest updates on the Russia-Ukraine war, visit our live blog:  Russia-Ukraine live